svg.text: Concept Explanation for SafeDocs Logo Grid1. Core IdeaThe SafeDocs logo is inspired by the concept of security and trust, drawing from the visual language of a safe lock a universal symbol of protection, preci-sion, and confidentiality. The design communicates that SafeDocs keeps your documents secure, verified, and easily accessible.2. Visual BreakdownA. Symbol FormationThe visual starts with S + Safe (Vault Image), combining the initial of the brand with the metaphor of a vault representing document protection.Together, these elements inspired the creation of the final circular grid, echoing the structure of a safes locking mechanism.B. Final Symbol (Grid)The concentric circular shapes represent layers of protection encryption, verification, and controlled access.The blue and orange arcs convey trust and innovation:Blue = Security, reliability, and professionalism.Orange = Accessibility, energy, and forward-thinking.The check mark at the center signifies verification and authenticity the assurance that every document in SafeDocs is genuine and secure.
